<recipe>
    <name>Arroz Mexicano</name>
    <indexCharacter>A</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>8</servings>
    <instructions>1. Heat oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add rice and cook, stirring occasionally for 3 or 4 minutes, until lightly golden brown. Reduce heat to medium. Add the onion, potato, garlic and salt. Cook and stir for about 2 minutes. Add the Goya sofrita; cook and stir for a minute or two and then slowly stir in the chicken broth.

2. Increase heat to medium-high and bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low, place a lid on the pan and simmer for 25 minutes. Remove from heat and allow to sit for 5 minutes, covered. Remove cover, fluff with a fork, garnish with cilantro (optional) and serve.</instructions>
